N2  - This paper discusses the planning horizon issues of the dynamic bond refunding problem, when interest, floatation and call costs are changing arbitrarily over time and are deterministic. A planning horizon theorem is proved, enabling us to identify planning and forecasting horizons and thus reducing information requirements and increasing computational efficiency.
